# =============================================================================
# Merge strategy for append-prone, machine-edited files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# `_data/backlog.yml` is the autopilot's shared to-do list. Every parallel
# content run appends a fresh item to the *end* of the same file, so two runs
# branched off the same `main` reliably collide on those final lines — the
# recurring "the one file the whole fleet fights over" merge conflict.
#
# The `union` merge driver resolves an append/append collision by keeping BOTH
# sides' lines instead of failing. Each run appends a distinct, well-formed
# YAML list item, so the union of two appends is still valid YAML — exactly the
# behaviour we want. Status flips and `published:` edits land on unique
# in-place lines and already merge cleanly; union only changes the outcome for
# the overlapping tail-append hunk.
#
# `union` is a built-in git driver (no `.git/config` setup needed); it is
# honoured by local `git merge`/`git rebase` and by GitHub's "Update branch".
# Scope it narrowly — never union-merge prose or structured config, where it
# would silently duplicate content.
# =============================================================================
_data/backlog.yml merge=union
